com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.type

Interface WebCmsTypeSpecifierService


  • public interface WebCmsTypeSpecifierService
    Service for retrieving WebCmsTypeSpecifier instances. Inspects the multi-domain configuration to determine which domains should be investigated for finding the type specifiers.
    Since:
    0.0.3
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme

      • getTypeSpecifier

        <T extends WebCmsTypeSpecifier> T getTypeSpecifier(String objectId,
                                                   Class<T> expectedType)
        Finds the type specifier with that object id, assuming it is of the expected java type. If type exists but not of the specified type, an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
        Type Parameters:
        T - expected type
        Parameters:
        objectId - the type specifier has
        expectedType - the type should have
        Returns:
        type specifier or null if not found

      • getTypeSpecifierByKey

        <T extends WebCmsTypeSpecifier> T getTypeSpecifierByKey(String typeKey,
                                                        Class<T> expectedType)
        Finds the type specifier represented by the type key, assuming it is of the expected java type. Requires all types to be registered in the WebCmsTypeRegistry.

        Will inspect the multi-domain configuration and use the current domain as well as fallback to no-domain if allowed for that type.

        Type Parameters:
        T - expected type
        Parameters:
        typeKey - of the type
        expectedType - output
        Returns:
        type specifier or null if not found

      • getTypeSpecifierByKey

        <T extends WebCmsTypeSpecifier> T getTypeSpecifierByKey(String typeKey,
                                                        Class<T> expectedType,
                                                        WebCmsDomain domain)
        Finds the type specifier represented by the type key, assuming it is of the expected java type. Requires all types to be registered in the WebCmsTypeRegistry.

        Will inspect the multi-domain configuration and use the current domain as well as fallback to no-domain if allowed for that type.

        Type Parameters:
        T - expected type
        Parameters:
        typeKey - of the type
        expectedType - output
        domain - to look for the type
        Returns:
        type specifier or null if not found
